00:14:04.479 --> 00:14:06.479
We're trying to toe the line of

00:14:06.479 --> 00:14:08.479
are we giving away company secrets to

00:14:08.479 --> 00:14:10.479
your own OpenTelemetry?

00:14:10.479 --> 00:14:12.479
But it's not the user, it's to you,

00:14:12.479 --> 00:14:14.479
so we'll see.

00:14:14.479 --> 00:14:16.479
This would also involve setting the

00:14:16.479 --> 00:14:18.479
status of the span, saying, oh, we had an

00:14:18.479 --> 00:14:20.479
error, I knew this was bad,

00:14:20.479 --> 00:14:22.479
let's set it to an error,

00:14:22.479 --> 00:14:24.479
versus saying it's unset or okay.

00:14:24.479 --> 00:14:26.479
I'd

00:14:26.479 --> 00:14:28.479
like to have native PositConnect

00:14:28.479 --> 00:14:30.479
integration.

00:14:30.479 --> 00:14:32.479
There's been a lot of work about

